        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 6:29PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 629 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bogus Basin Ski Area, or 9 miles southwest of Idaho City.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust possible. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northeastern Ada
and southwestern Boise Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
